laboratory_examinations.findings: White blood cell count normalized postoperatively.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: The white blood cell count trended to normal over the next several days.

laboratory_examinations.findings: ESR was the slowest to normalize, taking up to 3 weeks.
Fluid from both the operating room and the initial aspiration was negative for bacteria, fungi, and acid-fast bacilli.
Demonstrated periprosthetic fluid collection and communication to a larger, enhancing collection in the axilla.
